    "difficulty": "deep",
    "goal": "Keep deferred goals reachable and reject dependency cycles across the complete workspace.",
    "description": "Scope: Closure: capability - planning reachability integrity; own the Better Plan status contract, workspace prerequisite graph, manifest CLI lifecycle commands, focused acceptance tests, and matching public guidance. Context: skipped is simultaneously terminal history and documented future deferral, while executable prerequisite validation is confined to one checkpoint array and cannot see cross-Plan wait cycles. Target: add a visible resumable deferred state, reserve skipped for irreversible waiver, resolve every Node wait through workspace-wide prerequisites, and reject a complete cycle path before mutation or dispatch. Design Considerations: reuse globally unique Node UUIDs; use iterative O(V + E) DFS plus reverse-adjacency propagation; keep status_reason and next non-authoritative; validate proposed snapshots before atomic writes. Design Value: one authoritative reachability model prevents promised work from disappearing and prevents prose-level deadlocks from reaching an executor. Constraints & Risks: preserve terminal history, do not infer dependencies from prose, do not auto-select deferred work, do not expose machine or runtime data, do not add compatibility aliases or repeated full-regression gates.",
